1.title: Prom
1.plot: 18-year-old NASCAR prodigy Dylan struggles to balance his racing schedule in North Carolina and the end of his senior year of high school in Las Vegas. He rushes to get everything finished in time for his senior prom.

2.title: Two Worlds
2.plot: Before flying to North Carolina for training with his pit crew, Dylan and his best friend reminisce on their high school years. Dylan's mom, comes down hard on him for trying to split his time up between racing and his friends in Vegas.

3.title: Mr. Independent
3.plot: Dylan has a hard time adjusting to his new life and having his mom second-guess his decisions to take some time off. He visits his sister at college and gets a taste of the life he'll be missing out on.

4.title: A Bowman Gray Birthday
4.plot: On Dylan's 18th birthday, he reminisces about his father, who took his own life in 2010. His father's love for racing is Dylan's motivation for his own NASCAR dreams. That night, Dylan performs the unthinkable during a big race.

5.title: The Business
5.plot: Getting behind the wheel isn't Dylan's only focus as a racecar driver; he needs to focus on working with sponsors on the business end as well. The extra work throws a wrench into his plans to take a vacation with his best friend from high school.

6.title: Graduation
6.plot: Dylan is forced to miss his graduation for a race, and it hits him harder than he imagined. After the race, the organizers give him a mini-graduation at the track, he gets behind the wheel and pushes it during another nail-biting race.

7.title: Party Time
7.plot: On the eve of a big race, Dylan has a "small" house party and gets busted by his mom. His punishment leads to a breakthrough performance at crucial event in the circuit.

8.title: The Other Side
8.plot: Dylan moves into his own apartment and gains some independence. After spending time at the race shop, Dylan confides in his teammate about his uncertainties about moving to North Carolina and their shared fears about finding sponsorship.

9.title: Frenemies
9.plot: After he's almost wrecked on the track, Dylan realizes he needs to choose his friends carefully. Everyone he knows in Charlotte not only races, but is gunning for his spot.

10.title: The Call
10.plot: During a trip to the legendary Indianapolis Motor Speedway, Dylan gets advice from some of the top Sprint Cup drivers on how to take his career to the next level.

11.title: NASCAR Champions Week
11.plot: After a devastating wreck and races plagued with mechanical problems, Dylan finds himself desperate for a much-needed victory. Now only ahead by a tiny margin, Dylan must prove that he can overcome tremendous odds to clinch the championship win.

imdb.plot outline: Go behind-the-scenes with racing's hottest, young talent, 18-year-old Dylan Kwasniewski, as he aspires to make it in the #1 motorsport in America - NASCAR. Despite being only 18 years old, Dylan Kwasniewski is already a force to be reckoned with in the NASCAR world. After becoming the youngest driver to win the NASCAR K&N Pro Series West Championship in 2012, Dylan moved on to the NASCAR K&N Pro Series East and currently pilots the No. 98 Royal Purple/Rockstar Energy Chevrolet for Turner Scott Motorsports. After winning the season opening race at Bristol Motor Speedway, Kwasniewski currently leads the 2013 championship point standings.
